cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.IT, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the architecture of software defined radio prototypes for cognitive radio testbeds, which involves networking and communication technologies. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the organization and control of the prototypes. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the computing platforms used for the prototypes. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the transmission and processing of information in software defined radio systems. 
- cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper briefly mentions security issues in cognitive radio testbeds.
